d\nfor a distance modulus of (m-M)o = 10.69 indicate an age of log(t) = 7.90-8.00\nwith a slight tendency toward the younger age. Inspection of the shape of the\norbit of NGC 2302 and the resulting orbital parameters indicate that it is a\ntypical population I object.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 May 2015 21:17:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-06"}
